Next up in @dardensmithmusic’s "Who Said You Could Do That?" series that features intimate nights of music & conversation exploring the fascinating life paths of artists: @ginachavez on Thurs, 12/15 🎸🎶

“A Latin artist born in Austin to parents of Mexican and Swiss-German descent, her sound is as diverse as her background, incorporating bilingual lyrics with rock, pop, folk and cumbia beats. She’s also toured the world as a cultural ambassador for the U.S. State Department and is known for her philanthropic efforts and community activism. Having accumulated a mass of glowing accolades, the transcendent and traveled musician will give insight on impactful moments that have landed her 12 Austin Music Awards, a Latin Grammy nomination, chart-topping hits and a slew of high-profile performances from NPR’s Tiny Desk to The Kate on PBS.” - @tribeza

I just finished my first year as Vice President of the Texas Chapter of the @recordingacademy and I am excited to be up for re-election! ✨ To all members: Voting is OPEN through 3/30, so cast your ballots - the slate of candidates is truly amazing! 
.
Y’all I love the Texas Chapter. It’s such an honor to serve my community as the current Membership Chair, a GrammyU mentor and the DEI Ambassador for Texas. I’m committed to making our chapter (which is already so dope 👏🏽) a place where everyone can thrive, especially queer and non-binary folk, BIPOC members, indie artists and people who, like me, may not fit so easily into one genre category. It’s been an honor serving alongside our President @taylorhanson and a phenomenal Board of Directors. I welcome the opportunity to continue the work ☺️
.
Swipe right for a song I wrote about what it’s been like to serve on the board ☺️

🎶 Over the years, Gina Chavez has realized that having the courage to put music out in the world is the most beautiful part, regardless of the success. 

✨ “If you’re a creator and put yourself out there, that’s great. That’s the kind of greatness we need,” she proclaims. “You never know who you’re going to connect with. We all need someone to shine, so we can know that we, too, are bright.”

Монголчууд та бүхэн бэлэн үү? Дуучин @ginachavez Улаанбаатар хотыг зорин ирж буйг дуулгахад таатай байна! КҮИЙР, ЛАТИН, ТЕХАС тодотголтой хүчирхэг уран бүтээлчийг Монголд бидэнтэй хамт угтан аваарай! Дэлгэрэнгүй мэдээлэл тун удахгүй!

Get ready, Mongolia! Excited to announce that @ginachavez is coming to town! Join us as we welcome this QUEER. LATINX. TEXAN. powerhouse musician to Mongolia! Stay tuned for more updates!

Being queer was never cool. Or easy. Or sought after. It was a thing to hide, a part of myself to deny, to shut down, to pray away. So it’s hard to describe what it feels like to be invited to the other side of the world not just to play music, but to celebrate PRIDE through music; to celebrate the vibrant people of a beautiful and ancient land with every part of myself. I am queer and proud. And I’m headed to play PRIDE in Mongolia 🤯 Gracias a la vida 🙏🏽🏳️‍🌈🇲🇳 
.
Follow us for the next 10 days as we share music, culture and exactly who we are 👏🏽 
.
Photos by @brittanynofomo
Happy PRIDE from Mongolia 🇲🇳🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍🌈

Wow! What an life-changing and life-giving week celebrating PRIDE and Equality in Mongolia 🇲🇳🏳️‍🌈 photo dump (1st of many)
. 
1. My new favorite band photo! I could not have asked for a more thoughtful, giving, and amazingly talented band ✨ @kblizo (my twin lol) is a dream on trumpet and flugelhorn not to mention a heartbreaker on every tour 😉 @fearsontheinternet has the most buttery vocals and solos and the most welcoming presence ✨ @elimenezesgtr is the most down to earth badass I’ve ever met 🎸 and @joshuarobertsdrums was exactly what this tour called for - all l, chops for days and a truly beautiful heart 🫶🏽 
2. Raising our voices for change at the largest PRIDE night gathering in Mongolia 👏🏽 “Todo Cambia” never fails! 
3. With my new faves @sobo.artiste — a multi-talented singer, host and incredible human — and @thelanamunh — star of The Voice Mongolia and the most graceful, bright-shining star I’ve ever met ✨ 
4. Singing our Mongolian tribute Tolin Hul at salsa night where the crowd broke into a synchronized dance like we were in a movie 🤩 
5. Posing with @thelanamunh and the stars of Queer Theater in Mongolia 🙌🏽🏳️‍🌈
6. My heroes @jackganbaatar and @inkma of the @lgbtcentre.mongolia who have built a truly inclusive and incredible queer community in a place that continues to deny the rights of LGBTQIA+ people. 
7. Our first night in Mongolia qith @usembmongolia that brought us to expand human rights through PRIDE and Equality Days 🇺🇸🇲🇳🏳️‍🌈
8. Me and my camel at the infamous Chinggis Khan statue — largest equestrian statue in the world 🐎
9. Sexy queens 💋
10. La Que Manda at @fatcatjazzclub — a musically magic night I’ll never forget ✨
.
Harte Shuu Mongolia!
Missing Mongolia 🇲🇳😭 Bayirtla! Hiarte shu 🫶🏽
We’re missing our Mongolian friends today! Finally ✈️ back home after an absolutely incredible adventure abroad. Hairtai shuu! #ulaanbaatar #mongolia #pride #ginachavez

Today we were supposed to fly to #Morocco to sing with @faycalazizi and meet the beautiful people of Rabat, Casablanca and Tangier. Our hearts break for the people of Al Haouz and the thousands who lost their lives, loved ones and homes to the earthquake. May Allah bless Morocco 🇲🇦🙏🏽

@myhaam and the @longcenter bring you “A Night of Song and Storytelling” with @brenebrown and musicians, @ginachavez and @carrierockriguez, on Sunday, November 12, 2023.

Through the course of the evening, researcher, storyteller, and professor, author, podcast host, and Texan, Dr. Brené Brown and Austin musicians Gina Chavez and Carrie Rodriguez will use storytelling and song to explore the issues that make us human – love, loss, change, and hope.

Proceeds from ticket sales will benefit HAAM and its mission to provide access to affordable healthcare to Austin’s low-income, working musicians. Since 2005, HAAM has helped over 6,700 musicians access over $144M in healthcare services, including primary and specialty care, mental, dental, hearing, wellness, and vision services.

Tickets go on sale Tuesday, October 17, 2023, at 10 AM. Mark your calendars because tickets will go fast! We hope you’ll join us for this very special evening.

Greetings from the @recordingacademy mothership! It is an honor to serve our membership in Texas and beyond 🙏🏽 For those who don’t know much about the Recording Academy aside from the Grammys, we are a vibrant and passionate community of music-makers and professionals who are here to embrace each other, to listen, to ask the tough questions as we walk into the joys and challenges of serving our ever-growing membership. The board and staff truly blow my mind every time - thank you Recording Academy fam for embracing diverse voices and experience; for showing us what it means to take the next right step. Onward!
.
Now… remember to vote in the first round by tomorrow 10/22 🏆😉

Due to unforeseen circumstances, “A Night of Song of Song and Storytelling” with Brené Brown, Gina Chavez, and Carrie Rodriguez is being moved to April 2, 2024. Your tickets will be transferred and honored at the new date. If you are unable to attend the show, we are happy to refund your tickets (please contact the Long Center directly). We apologize for any inconvenience and look forward to seeing you in the Spring.
